"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-team-gb-great-britain-britain-paris-tom-pidcock-b2594766.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Britainfinished seventh on the Olympic medal table asParis2024 wrapped up on Sunday.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GBwon 14 golds while their 65 total medals were the third-most of any team, behind theUnited Statesand China and one ahead of hosts France.\", \"from\": 432, \"to\": 576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 540, \"end\": 545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.7889224794351033, \"rank\": 0.2674294858539471, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here, the PA news agency looks at where the prizes were won.\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As so often, cycling proved to be Britain's most successful sport with 11 medals thanks to the combination of a high number of events and Team GB's strength across the programme.\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 818, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 674, \"end\": 681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999991990715468, \"rank\": 8.00928996293264e-07, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 778, \"end\": 785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999970441, \"rank\": 2.8905476933139806e-12, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Golds forTom Pidcockon the mountain and the women's track sprint team of Katy Marchant, Sophie Capewell and Emma Finucane were backed up by five silver and four bronze medals - including two of the latter for Finucane, one of the star performers of these Games.\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 1081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 893, \"end\": 906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katy Marchant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\"}, {\"begin\": 908, \"end\": 923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\", \"score\": 0.999997246383526, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sophie Capewell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\"}, {\"begin\": 928, \"end\": 932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.6552213570196522, \"rank\": 0.4980476849881452, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletics also saw a double-figure haul, the highlight being Keely Hodgkinson's 800 metres gold.\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1179, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1144, \"end\": 1160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain won medals in all five relays - four bronzes, and silver in the women's 4x100m.\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1180, \"end\": 1187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999991990715468, \"rank\": 8.00928996293264e-07, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB's rowers made a major return to form with three gold, two silver and three bronze medals.\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1269, \"end\": 1276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999970441, \"rank\": 2.8905476933139806e-12, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold came from the men's eight and the women's quadruple sculls and lightweight double sculls.\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1462, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's pair and the men's quadruple sculls were the only British boats not to win medals, with the latter finishing fourth.\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1525, \"end\": 1532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999968636915652, \"rank\": 3.079212959413754e-06, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Equestrian was another typical success story, despite the pre-Games controversy around Charlotte Dujardin, with team golds in eventing and jumping and bronze for Laura Collett in jumping and for the team and Charlotte Fry individually in dressage.\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1680, \"end\": 1698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Dujardin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\"}, {\"begin\": 1755, \"end\": 1768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"score\": 0.9999948522782397, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Collett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\"}, {\"begin\": 1801, \"end\": 1814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Fry\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Fry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Fry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Fry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were medals in all three triathlon events, including individual gold for Alex Yee, while swimming brought four silvers plus men's 4x200m freestyle gold.\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 2000, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1921, \"end\": 1929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Yee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB took medals in 17 of the 25 sports in which they were represented, with gold in 10 of those.\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2002, \"end\": 2009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999970441, \"rank\": 2.8905476933139806e-12, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Toby Roberts won Britain's first ever sport climbing medal, and gold to boot, while gymnastics, sailing and shooting were the other sports to yield top spot.\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2104, \"end\": 2108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\", \"score\": 0.9963443820782277, \"rank\": 0.0034796915091972174, \"text\": \"Toby\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Animorphs\"}, {\"begin\": 2121, \"end\": 2128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999991990715468, \"rank\": 8.00928996293264e-07, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Diving brought five medals and canoeing four but no golds, while Lewis Richardson's bronze salvaged an otherwise dismal boxing effort.\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2328, \"end\": 2344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_Richardson_(Hollyoaks)\", \"score\": 0.9965136461602875, \"rank\": 0.0034965034965027397, \"text\": \"Lewis Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_Richardson_(Hollyoaks)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_Richardson_(Hollyoaks)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain's lone weightlifter, Emily Campbell, won the team's final medal of the Games on the last day of competition.\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2514, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2398, \"end\": 2405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999991990715468, \"rank\": 8.00928996293264e-07, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2427, \"end\": 2441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Campbell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emily Campbell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Campbell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Campbell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Archery, badminton, hockey, judo, modern pentathlon, rugby sevens, table tennis and tennis were the only sports not to bring home at least one medal.\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2665, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Of Team GB's 14 gold medals, six each came in men's and women's events and two in mixed equestrian events, where male and female riders compete together - though the team jumping was won by an all-male trio of Scott Brash, Harry Charles and Ben Maher.\", \"from\": 2667, \"to\": 2918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2755, \"end\": 2765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9989858976349588, \"rank\": 0.001013175104703545, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2877, \"end\": 2888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Brash\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scott Brash\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Brash\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Brash\"}, {\"begin\": 2908, \"end\": 2917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Maher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ben Maher\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Maher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Maher\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Men won 15 silvers to the women's seven but there were 15 women's bronze medals to nine in men's events, plus equestrian duo Charlotte Fry and Laura Collett winning two of the five bronze medals from mixed events.\", \"from\": 2920, \"to\": 3133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3030, \"end\": 3040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9989858976349588, \"rank\": 0.001013175104703545, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3045, \"end\": 3058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Fry\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Fry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Fry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Fry\"}, {\"begin\": 3063, \"end\": 3076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"score\": 0.9999948522782397, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Collett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In terms of medals won by individual athletes - a larger total recognising each member of a winning team - male and female British athletes will each return home with 68 medals in their luggage.\", \"from\": 3135, \"to\": 3329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3258, \"end\": 3265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999968636915652, \"rank\": 3.079212959413754e-06, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The male total features seven more golds than for the female members of the squad, 21 to 14, despite women making up the majority of the British squad for the second successive Olympics, 172 to 156.\", \"from\": 3331, \"to\": 3529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3468, \"end\": 3475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999968636915652, \"rank\": 3.079212959413754e-06, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Henry Fielding, the male cox of the bronze medal-winning women's eight in rowing, became the first person ever to win Olympic medals in both male and female events after guiding the men's eight to bronze at Tokyo 2020.\", \"from\": 3531, \"to\": 3749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3531, \"end\": 3545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Fielding\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2188208776854982e-20, \"text\": \"Henry Fielding\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Fielding\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Fielding\"}, {\"begin\": 3738, \"end\": 3743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999947576725, \"rank\": 5.242418659512754e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3751, \"to\": 3887, \"entities\": []}]}"